[^AUTHOR: DAVYS, MARY.
TEXT: THE REFORM'D COQUET; A NOVEL.
IN: THE WORKS OF MRS. DAVYS: CONSISTING OF PLAYS, NOVELS, POEMS, AND
FAMILIAR LETTERS. SEVERAL OF WHICH NEVER BEFORE PUBLISH'D.
VOL. II. CONTAINING, 
I. THE REFORM'D COQUET; A NOVEL. 
II. THE LADY'S TALE.
III. THE COUSINS; A NOVEL.
IV. FAMILIAR LETTERS BETWIXT A GENTLEMAN AND A LADY.
LONDON, PRINTED BY H. WOODFALL, FOR THE AUTHOR: AND SOLD BY J. 
STEVENS, AT THE BIBLE IN BUTCHER-ROW, NEAR ST. CLEMENT'S CHURCH; AND
BY THE BOOKSELLERS OF LONDON AND WESTMINSTER.
